<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <style>
        body {
            font: 14px/18px "HelveticaNeue", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            color: #000000;
        }
        
        h2 { color: #4DB8FF; }
    .auto-style2 {
		font-family: Arial;
	}
	.auto-style5 {
		font-size: medium;
		font-family: "Times New Roman";
		color: #4DB8FF;
	}
	.auto-style6 {
		font-size: small;
		font-family: "Times New Roman";
	}
	.auto-style7 {
		color: #4DB8FF;
	}
	.auto-style8 {
		text-decoration: none;
	}
    </style>
	
	    <script type="text/javascript">
     
    function toggle(id) {
      var e = document.getElementById(id);
     
      if (e.style.display == '')
        e.style.display = 'none';
      else
        e.style.display = '';
    }
     
    </script>

</head>
<body style="height: 344px">
<div id="secondary">
    <h2 class="auto-style2">Consult Help!</h2>
    
    <p class="auto-style6">The Consult page helps you create and find the Consultation details of a patient. For a Patient's a test consultation you can begin with searching a patient for whom test requests are to be created.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
		<p class="auto-style5">
		<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node1')" class="auto-style8">
		<span class="auto-style7">Patient Search</span></a></p>
		<dl id="node1" style="display:none">
			
			<p class="auto-style6">Patient search has three fields in which you can enter the input for any or all or combination of the three fields to search for a patient record.<ul class="auto-style6"><li>Enter a patient number.</li> <li>And /Or enter the patient name - remember to enter it as (lastname,firstname).</li><li>And /Or enter Date of birth, select a date using the date picker, you cannot enter. In the date picker you can click on the month-year displayed between the left and right arrows for more options to select, to enter.</li><li> In case you make any mistakes you can reset the fields by using the 'reset' button.</li><li>you can now click on the 'submit' button and retrieve your patient record.</li></ul></p>
		
		</dl>
		</li>
		
		<li>
		<p class="auto-style5">
		<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node2')" class="auto-style8">
		<span class="auto-style7">Patient Details</span></a></p>
		<dl  id="node2" style="display:none">
		
			<p class="auto-style6">This page displays the patient details of the patient you searched for. <ul class="auto-style6"><li>You can click on 'Consultations' and find out if the patient has any consultations.</li> <li>You can click 'Back' button to return back and search for a new patient.</li></ul></p>
		
		</dl>
		</li>
		
		<li>
			<p class="auto-style5">
			<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node3')" class="auto-style8">
			<span class="auto-style7">Consultations</span></a></p>
		</li>
		<dl id="node3" style="display:none">
		
			<p class="auto-style6">This page gives all the patient consultations that exists for the particular patient, in a table. You can choose any of the records and alert for the consultation. 
				<ul class="auto-style6">
						<li>If a consultations exists for the patient: a table is displayed, else the page has just two buttons i.e. 'New consultation' button to create a new consultation for the patient and a 'Back' button to go back to the patient details page.</li>
						<li>In the table associated with each consultation is a radio button which upon choosing you may perform the alerting operation.</li> 
                                                <li>There is a search option above the table. By entering the search keyword you could filter the list of records being displayed to match the entered criteria</li>
						<li>The 'Alert' button lets you set an alert for the test request and intimate the required people.</li>
						<li>You also have two buttons at the bottom of the page which are not associated with any consultations i.e. 'New consultation' button and a 'Back' button.</li>
				</ul>
			</p>
		
		</dl>		

		<li>
			<p class="auto-style5">
			<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node7')" class="auto-style8">
			<span class="auto-style7">Create New Consultation</span></a></p>
		</li>
		<dl id="node7" style="display:none">
		
			<p class="auto-style6">This page upon successfully completing adds a new consultation to the patient 
				<ul class="auto-style6">
						<li>You have a list of fields and its corresponding values for the patient consultation that are to be filled up.</li>
						<li> The date field can only be picked from the date picker and cannot be manually entered.</li>
						<li> All filed names preceeding with a '*' mark are required to be filled, others can be left blank.</li>
						<li> The 'User Name' field gets auto filled and the user cannot edit this field.</li>
						<li>In the end of the page you have an 'Save' button which when clicked takes you to the earlier Consultations page.</li> 
				</ul>
			</p>		
		</dl>
		
	</ul>
    
</div>
    
</body>
</html>